1
00:00:27,350 --> 00:00:28,610
Get out of here. Quick.

2
00:00:29,620 --> 00:00:30,680
Take precautions!

3
00:00:31,920 --> 00:00:32,710
Hurry and go!

4
00:00:33,150 --> 00:00:34,700
Hurry, or you'll all die.

5
00:00:35,480 --> 00:00:35,950
Go!

6
00:00:37,520 --> 00:00:38,490
Don't go in.

7
00:00:38,670 --> 00:00:40,150
You'll die if you touch those things.

8
00:00:40,150 --> 00:00:40,960
They won't touch us.

9
00:00:40,960 --> 00:00:41,420
Don't go in.

10
00:00:41,420 --> 00:00:42,150
Don't worry.

11
00:00:42,820 --> 00:00:44,280
-Don't go in.
-Don't go in.

12
00:01:12,170 --> 00:01:14,100
There's a stench of rotting flesh.

13
00:01:18,020 --> 00:01:18,780
Shrimpie.

14
00:01:18,070 --> 00:01:22,280
[Inside the Ming Dynasty Shipwreck]

15
00:01:18,800 --> 00:01:20,590
Look, the ship's turned to stone.

16
00:01:20,590 --> 00:01:21,930
The reef and the hull are stuck together.

17
00:01:21,930 --> 00:01:22,789
We can barely see anything.

18
00:01:22,789 --> 00:01:25,760
It really looks like a sunken ship
from the Ming Dynasty.

19
00:01:25,760 --> 00:01:26,690
Stop analyzing.

20
00:01:26,870 --> 00:01:28,480
It's surrounded by seawater.

21
00:01:28,480 --> 00:01:29,310
It's been here too long

22
00:01:29,310 --> 00:01:30,840
and could easily collapse.

23
00:01:31,039 --> 00:01:32,170
Let's move quickly.

24
00:01:42,270 --> 00:01:44,530
The bodies in these bags have all rotted.

25
00:01:46,259 --> 00:01:46,810
Why did the ancient people

26
00:01:46,810 --> 00:01:48,450
hang up these corpses?

27
00:01:49,520 --> 00:01:50,509
Look here.

28
00:01:51,229 --> 00:01:52,660
If I'm not mistaken,

29
00:01:52,700 --> 00:01:54,000
they hung up the bodies

30
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:55,690
to collect bodily fluids

31
00:01:55,970 --> 00:01:57,500
and nourish these plants.

32
00:02:17,500 --> 00:02:19,230
A Ming Dynasty nautical chart.

33
00:02:19,930 --> 00:02:22,260
No wonder these corpses rotted like that.

34
00:02:22,780 --> 00:02:25,110
It might belong
to the crew from that time.

35
00:02:25,370 --> 00:02:27,770
They probably hung
these body bags up, too.

36
00:02:28,450 --> 00:02:30,000
[On the day of departure, the sea
and sky were clear, and the waters were calm]

37
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:31,500
[More than a hundred people aboard
attended to their duties in good order]

38
00:02:32,650 --> 00:02:34,540
It also records a strange event.

39
00:02:34,660 --> 00:02:36,130
[On the seventh day of the voyage,
strange things happened]

40
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:38,560
It says that when the ship set sail,

41
00:02:38,579 --> 00:02:41,110
the crew suddenly began
to die mysteriously.

42
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:43,410
Each victim developed
red rashes across the body

43
00:02:43,410 --> 00:02:45,240
and died as their flesh
gradually ulcerated.

44
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:46,960
As more and more people died,

45
00:02:47,150 --> 00:02:48,780
the whole crew panicked.

46
00:02:49,240 --> 00:02:50,500
What's wrong, Mr. San?

47
00:02:50,560 --> 00:02:51,290
This ship...

48
00:02:52,090 --> 00:02:53,960
This ship is haunted by water ghosts.

49
00:02:53,960 --> 00:02:56,060
Water ghosts. The water ghosts are here!

50
00:02:56,060 --> 00:02:57,950
The souls of those you sank into the sea

51
00:02:57,950 --> 00:03:00,900
will be trapped upon the waters,
unable to return home.

52
00:03:00,900 --> 00:03:01,500
So,

53
00:03:02,120 --> 00:03:03,310
they turned into evil spirits

54
00:03:03,310 --> 00:03:05,390
and came back
to the ship to claim our lives!

55
00:03:05,390 --> 00:03:07,200
Mr. San, what should we do?

56
00:03:09,150 --> 00:03:11,280
Hang up all the corpses—

57
00:03:11,560 --> 00:03:13,390
trap the evil spirits inside the corpses.

58
00:03:13,390 --> 00:03:14,290
Once we dock,

59
00:03:14,410 --> 00:03:15,900
give them a proper burial.

60
00:03:16,290 --> 00:03:17,040
Remember,

61
00:03:17,120 --> 00:03:18,210
the feet of the corpses

62
00:03:18,210 --> 00:03:20,140
must never touch the deck.

63
00:03:20,310 --> 00:03:22,570
Black water dripped from these corpses,

64
00:03:22,850 --> 00:03:24,780
which actually worsened the disaster.

65
00:03:24,300 --> 00:03:28,240
[A few months later]

66
00:03:46,190 --> 00:03:47,000
It must be that, back then,

67
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:49,310
someone on the ship
was poisoned by Twilight Grass.

68
00:03:49,310 --> 00:03:50,980
Those poisoned people

69
00:03:51,020 --> 00:03:52,570
were tainted with the seeds
of Twilight Grass.

70
00:03:52,570 --> 00:03:53,850
After they died,

71
00:03:54,030 --> 00:03:55,829
the seeds grew on their corpses.

72
00:03:56,240 --> 00:03:58,930
Twilight Grass likes
a dark and humid environment,

73
00:03:58,930 --> 00:04:00,590
and the cabin perfectly fits.

74
00:04:00,710 --> 00:04:01,530
Day by day,

75
00:04:01,650 --> 00:04:03,280
Twilight Grass spread throughout the ship,

76
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:05,280
causing tragedy for the whole ship.

77
00:04:05,520 --> 00:04:06,620
This black bodily fluid

78
00:04:06,620 --> 00:04:08,430
must contain Twilight Grass seeds.

79
00:04:08,430 --> 00:04:10,080
Otherwise, there wouldn't be
so many of these plants.

80
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:11,960
This is the essence of this ship—

81
00:04:12,240 --> 00:04:14,030
the concentrated bodily fluid

82
00:04:15,960 --> 00:04:17,620
of those who died from poison.

83
00:04:23,980 --> 00:04:25,180
What do you want to do?

84
00:04:27,010 --> 00:04:29,610
Those bastards up there
definitely want this.

85
00:04:30,600 --> 00:04:31,930
Such a dangerous thing—

86
00:04:32,630 --> 00:04:34,830
how can we let it stay and harm the world?

87
00:04:35,100 --> 00:04:36,300
Let me disinfect you.

88
00:04:36,360 --> 00:04:38,090
Looks like you're enjoying it.

89
00:04:38,240 --> 00:04:38,860
Really?

90
00:04:39,070 --> 00:04:40,130
Is it that obvious?

91
00:04:40,540 --> 00:04:41,240
You guys,

92
00:04:41,330 --> 00:04:42,390
go help over there!

93
00:04:42,690 --> 00:04:43,130
Hurry!

94
00:04:43,680 --> 00:04:44,100
Go!

95
00:04:44,420 --> 00:04:44,950
Yes, sir.

96
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:45,530
Yes, sir.

97
00:04:48,010 --> 00:04:49,670
Adjutant Chen, what's wrong?

98
00:04:50,680 --> 00:04:51,700
Why is it such a mess here?

99
00:04:51,700 --> 00:04:53,180
You ordered us to blast the reef cave.

100
00:04:53,180 --> 00:04:54,630
Now that the reef is blown open,

101
00:04:54,630 --> 00:04:55,590
something came out.

102
00:04:55,590 --> 00:04:57,560
Our men suffered heavy casualties.

103
00:04:57,560 --> 00:04:59,490
Did Salty Zhang hurt you like this?

104
00:04:59,810 --> 00:05:00,570
Who?

105
00:05:01,300 --> 00:05:02,150
Salty Zhang.

106
00:05:02,750 --> 00:05:04,950
Your lifelong nemesis.

107
00:05:05,870 --> 00:05:08,190
Salty Zhang...

108
00:05:09,660 --> 00:05:11,620
The Commander and I have worked hard
on this for so many years.

109
00:05:11,620 --> 00:05:13,280
We can't let them take it away.

110
00:05:15,190 --> 00:05:16,840
Even if I die,

111
00:05:17,890 --> 00:05:20,670
I will get those seeds back for you.

112
00:05:24,720 --> 00:05:25,780
Someone is coming.

113
00:05:42,220 --> 00:05:44,100
I should have finished this kid
off just now.

114
00:05:44,100 --> 00:05:45,240
What a mistake.

115
00:06:14,630 --> 00:06:16,430
Burn all the evidence.

116
00:06:16,480 --> 00:06:18,240
Don't let anyone go!

117
00:06:32,630 --> 00:06:34,430
The only exit is blocked by them.

118
00:06:49,470 --> 00:06:51,270
You want to use the bomb
to blow open the hull

119
00:06:51,270 --> 00:06:53,800
and use the shockwave
to blast us into the sea?

120
00:06:53,860 --> 00:06:54,659
You're crazy.

121
00:06:54,980 --> 00:06:55,860
Let's try.

122
00:06:56,430 --> 00:06:57,370
Leave it to fate.

123
00:06:58,670 --> 00:06:59,760
Leave it to fate.

124
00:07:14,890 --> 00:07:16,510
Throw all the bombs over there!

125
00:07:16,510 --> 00:07:17,470
Blow them up!

126
00:07:25,220 --> 00:07:27,020
I didn't expect such heavy fire.

127
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:27,830
Can this thing

128
00:07:27,830 --> 00:07:28,910
even hold up?

129
00:07:29,930 --> 00:07:31,440
Do you want to go back to Xiacheng?

130
00:07:31,440 --> 00:07:32,900
Nonsense. Of course, I do.

131
00:07:37,940 --> 00:07:38,800
Okay.

132
00:07:43,070 --> 00:07:44,000
What do you mean?

133
00:07:44,440 --> 00:07:45,240
Zhang Hailou.

134
00:07:46,880 --> 00:07:48,480
I don't want to go back there.

135
00:07:49,450 --> 00:07:51,450
I have nothing left to hold me there.

136
00:07:53,510 --> 00:07:54,770
You go back in my place.

137
00:07:55,659 --> 00:07:56,310
Shrimpie,

138
00:07:56,580 --> 00:07:57,630
can you stop—

139
00:08:00,870 --> 00:08:02,730
Zhang Haixia, what are you doing?

140
00:08:08,350 --> 00:08:09,450
Shrimpie,

141
00:08:09,770 --> 00:08:10,920
are you crazy?

142
00:09:44,580 --> 00:09:50,850
[Archives: The Nanyang Mystery]

143
00:09:51,310 --> 00:09:53,890
[Episode 3]

144
00:10:04,030 --> 00:10:04,960
Shrimpie.

145
00:10:06,030 --> 00:10:06,820
Shrimpie.

146
00:10:10,080 --> 00:10:10,750
Shrimpie.

147
00:10:11,640 --> 00:10:12,370
Shrimpie.

148
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:25,670
Shrimpie.

149
00:10:26,940 --> 00:10:27,670
Shrimpie.

150
00:10:28,140 --> 00:10:28,900
Shrimpie.

151
00:10:33,700 --> 00:10:35,030
Shrimpie, stay with me.

152
00:10:35,910 --> 00:10:37,040
I'm taking you home.

153
00:10:40,390 --> 00:10:43,200
Then have you ever thought about
the people around you?

154
00:10:43,200 --> 00:10:44,330
You've had your fun,

155
00:10:45,220 --> 00:10:46,820
but what about the rest of us?

156
00:11:30,170 --> 00:11:32,030
Do you want to go back to Xiacheng?

157
00:11:33,390 --> 00:11:34,790
Nonsense. Of course, I do.

158
00:11:34,790 --> 00:11:36,390
I don't want to go back there.

159
00:11:37,170 --> 00:11:39,170
I have nothing left to hold me there.

160
00:11:41,410 --> 00:11:42,670
You go back in my place.

161
00:11:53,410 --> 00:11:55,270
Zhang Haixia, what are you doing?

162
00:12:23,020 --> 00:12:24,230
[A Hundred Flowers in Bloom]

163
00:12:24,270 --> 00:12:27,670
[A dozen years ago]
[The Zhang Residence, Xiacheng]

164
00:12:35,110 --> 00:12:35,780
Mentor.

165
00:12:39,690 --> 00:12:40,540
Zhang Hailou,

166
00:12:40,920 --> 00:12:42,120
what are you drawing?

167
00:12:42,820 --> 00:12:44,620
A thrush. Looks like one, right?

168
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:53,860
Zhang Haixia,
what's wrong with your eyebrows?

169
00:12:55,610 --> 00:12:57,140
Go wash off those eyebrows.

170
00:13:14,390 --> 00:13:15,860
This is your true nature.

171
00:13:17,320 --> 00:13:18,890
Your true nature is a snake.

172
00:13:19,400 --> 00:13:20,260
A snake

173
00:13:20,480 --> 00:13:21,880
will devour everything.

174
00:13:26,010 --> 00:13:27,440
But you can't be blamed for this.

175
00:13:27,440 --> 00:13:28,970
Luckily, you had dumb luck,

176
00:13:29,250 --> 00:13:31,110
having Zhang Haixia by your side—

177
00:13:31,270 --> 00:13:32,330
he will remind you.

178
00:13:38,910 --> 00:13:39,910
Did you hear that?

179
00:13:40,540 --> 00:13:41,730
Be nicer to me.

180
00:14:09,150 --> 00:14:09,980
Help!

181
00:14:12,600 --> 00:14:13,580
Help!

182
00:14:20,390 --> 00:14:23,330
[Beilian Wharf]

183
00:14:21,290 --> 00:14:21,950
Commander.

184
00:14:22,340 --> 00:14:24,840
The ship departed
from Panhua Reef half a month ago

185
00:14:24,840 --> 00:14:26,580
and just arrived at the port today.

186
00:14:26,580 --> 00:14:28,910
This is a letter written by Adjutant Chen.

187
00:14:31,510 --> 00:14:32,670
Dear Commander,

188
00:14:33,030 --> 00:14:34,030
after ten years of wandering,

189
00:14:34,030 --> 00:14:35,670
fortunately, I did not fail your trust.

190
00:14:35,670 --> 00:14:37,390
I've obtained the Twilight Grass seeds,

191
00:14:37,390 --> 00:14:39,190
completing your instructions.

192
00:14:39,720 --> 00:14:40,960
Please be careful

193
00:14:40,960 --> 00:14:44,580
of the Southern Archives under
the Maritime Supervisory Office.

194
00:14:44,580 --> 00:14:46,770
The person I encountered at Panhua Reef

195
00:14:46,770 --> 00:14:49,230
was Salty Zhang,
an agent from the Archives.

196
00:14:49,410 --> 00:14:50,270
Additionally,

197
00:14:50,530 --> 00:14:52,480
the Twilight Grass Poison has spread,

198
00:14:52,480 --> 00:14:54,270
infecting all the soldiers in the fleet.

199
00:14:54,270 --> 00:14:56,270
Everyone else has been eliminated.

200
00:14:56,530 --> 00:14:59,060
The soldiers on the ship
must not be kept alive

201
00:14:59,250 --> 00:15:00,780
to prevent future trouble.

202
00:15:01,460 --> 00:15:02,220
Commander,

203
00:15:03,100 --> 00:15:05,290
Adjutant Chen's body has stiffened.

204
00:15:05,370 --> 00:15:06,810
We can't get the jar off.

205
00:15:08,360 --> 00:15:09,650
What is the axe for?

206
00:15:10,390 --> 00:15:11,370
Chop off his hand

207
00:15:11,720 --> 00:15:12,840
and take the jar.

208
00:15:23,980 --> 00:15:25,390
The so-called

209
00:15:26,150 --> 00:15:28,540
[Mo Yungao, Leader
of the Mo Warlord Faction of Beilian]

210
00:15:26,360 --> 00:15:28,940
Southern Archives

211
00:15:29,870 --> 00:15:30,870
under the Nanyang

212
00:15:31,890 --> 00:15:33,620
Maritime Supervisory Office—

213
00:15:34,630 --> 00:15:36,560
investigate it thoroughly, okay?

214
00:15:37,120 --> 00:15:38,330
After finding them,

215
00:15:37,220 --> 00:15:39,610
[Lu Junxiang, Adjutant
in the Mo Warlord Faction of Beilian]

216
00:15:38,530 --> 00:15:40,130
how should we deal with them?

217
00:15:42,410 --> 00:15:44,050
In the letter, he said

218
00:15:45,130 --> 00:15:47,340
that the man is called Salty Zhang.

219
00:15:48,460 --> 00:15:49,670
His surname is Zhang.

220
00:16:11,900 --> 00:16:13,370
A member of the Zhang family.

221
00:16:13,370 --> 00:16:15,610
I have finally found you.

222
00:16:28,670 --> 00:16:31,680
By any means necessary,

223
00:16:32,370 --> 00:16:34,430
find everyone in the Archives for me.

224
00:16:48,380 --> 00:16:54,560
[Mo Yungao's Special Train]

225
00:16:48,480 --> 00:16:49,150
Commander.

226
00:16:51,150 --> 00:16:53,940
I have investigated everywhere.

227
00:16:54,650 --> 00:16:57,050
But didn't find
the so-called Southern Archives.

228
00:16:57,050 --> 00:16:58,700
We caught some people

229
00:16:58,720 --> 00:17:00,620
who are suspected members of the Archives.

230
00:17:00,620 --> 00:17:02,480
Some of them revealed a few clues.

231
00:17:14,740 --> 00:17:15,460
The Southern Archives

232
00:17:15,460 --> 00:17:17,349
is an organization that specializes
in investigating mysterious incidents.

233
00:17:17,349 --> 00:17:19,020
It originated

234
00:17:19,119 --> 00:17:20,780
from an ancient Zhang family.

235
00:17:21,200 --> 00:17:22,069
That family

236
00:17:22,250 --> 00:17:23,310
is very mysterious

237
00:17:24,069 --> 00:17:25,730
and has extraordinary power.

238
00:17:27,050 --> 00:17:28,170
The leader

239
00:17:28,690 --> 00:17:29,780
of the Archives

240
00:17:29,810 --> 00:17:31,110
is Zhang Haiqi.

241
00:17:34,550 --> 00:17:35,850
Zhang Haiqi.

242
00:17:38,160 --> 00:17:39,570
In the Panhua Reef Case,

243
00:17:40,240 --> 00:17:41,420
the advisor's prophecy

244
00:17:41,420 --> 00:17:42,880
was almost fully realized.

245
00:17:42,880 --> 00:17:45,420
The case ended
with two agents critically injured

246
00:17:45,420 --> 00:17:46,820
and remains unresolved.

247
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:49,060
What they did not expect was that,

248
00:17:49,240 --> 00:17:50,990
during their recovery,

249
00:17:51,420 --> 00:17:53,510
the Balongzhou Branch
of the Southern Archives

250
00:17:53,510 --> 00:17:55,770
was suddenly ordered
to suspend all operations.

251
00:17:55,770 --> 00:17:57,690
All personnel were dismissed

252
00:17:58,020 --> 00:18:00,220
and instructed to recover on their own.

253
00:18:02,460 --> 00:18:06,390
[Notice of Closure—
Maritime Supervisory Office]

254
00:18:08,530 --> 00:18:11,590
Zhang Hailou kept trying
to contact the headquarters,

255
00:18:11,820 --> 00:18:14,450
but never received any reply.

256
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:41,730
Where have all the people
from the Archives gone?

257
00:18:41,920 --> 00:18:43,720
Why didn't even Mentor respond?

258
00:18:46,840 --> 00:18:50,120
[Balai Rainforest]

259
00:18:48,330 --> 00:18:49,400
Time passed.

260
00:18:50,400 --> 00:18:52,930
In the three years
since the Panhua Reef case,

261
00:18:53,020 --> 00:18:54,570
members of the Southern Archives
in various branches

262
00:18:54,570 --> 00:18:56,980
went missing one after another.

263
00:18:58,070 --> 00:19:00,230
Zhang Haiqi,
the director of the Archives,

264
00:19:00,230 --> 00:19:01,760
has been investigating it.

265
00:19:22,700 --> 00:19:25,620
Who hung those bodies up?

266
00:19:25,680 --> 00:19:26,470
I don't know.

267
00:19:26,860 --> 00:19:28,240
It seems they offended someone

268
00:19:28,240 --> 00:19:31,340
and were hung up in revenge.
They've been hanging for a long time.

269
00:19:31,340 --> 00:19:33,460
I heard they were still alive
when they were just hung up.

270
00:19:33,460 --> 00:19:35,660
Their screams could be heard every day.

271
00:19:37,280 --> 00:19:38,480
Drive the car over.

272
00:20:25,520 --> 00:20:27,920
Why did you kill the people
of the Archives?

273
00:20:51,970 --> 00:20:53,130
Who are you?

274
00:20:53,230 --> 00:20:54,410
Who betrayed the Archives?

275
00:20:54,410 --> 00:20:55,800
You don't need to know.

276
00:20:55,830 --> 00:20:57,210
You won't live anyway.

277
00:21:26,710 --> 00:21:29,240
I won't let you die
without knowing the truth.

278
00:21:30,600 --> 00:21:32,970
[Nanyang Maritime Supervisory Office]

279
00:21:44,940 --> 00:21:54,410
[Nanyang Daily]

280
00:21:56,720 --> 00:21:59,120
Are you still thinking about these things?

281
00:22:02,380 --> 00:22:03,220
Over the years,

282
00:22:03,220 --> 00:22:05,900
I've looked into many plants related
to Twilight Grass.

283
00:22:05,900 --> 00:22:07,100
But later, I found out

284
00:22:07,160 --> 00:22:08,400
that the last time Twilight Grass appeared

285
00:22:08,400 --> 00:22:10,000
was in the late Ming Dynasty.

286
00:22:10,380 --> 00:22:11,590
This grass, from root to seed,

287
00:22:11,590 --> 00:22:12,520
is highly toxic.

288
00:22:12,980 --> 00:22:14,000
The fact that we survived

289
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:15,660
is nothing short of a miracle.

290
00:22:16,720 --> 00:22:18,850
It's been so long since this happened.

291
00:22:19,530 --> 00:22:21,860
Is it meaningful
for you to think about it?

292
00:22:25,700 --> 00:22:26,380
How is it?

293
00:22:27,160 --> 00:22:28,850
Still no news from headquarters?

294
00:22:28,850 --> 00:22:30,060
Not only no news,

295
00:22:30,290 --> 00:22:31,670
but they haven't even paid us.

296
00:22:31,670 --> 00:22:34,130
Do you think the Archives
will be disbanded?

297
00:22:34,240 --> 00:22:35,340
If it is disbanded,

298
00:22:35,940 --> 00:22:37,070
what are your plans?

299
00:22:37,180 --> 00:22:38,010
I think

300
00:22:38,450 --> 00:22:41,980
we need to go back to Xiacheng
to find Mentor as soon as possible.

301
00:22:42,570 --> 00:22:43,710
If it weren't for me,

302
00:22:44,570 --> 00:22:46,350
you could have gone back
to Xiacheng a long time ago.

303
00:22:46,350 --> 00:22:47,480
Don't say that.

304
00:22:47,960 --> 00:22:50,240
When we get back
to Xiacheng and find Mentor,

305
00:22:50,240 --> 00:22:51,000
I'm sure she'll

306
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:52,330
be able to cure your leg.

307
00:23:00,400 --> 00:23:01,630
Even if she can't,

308
00:23:02,080 --> 00:23:03,080
you still have me.

309
00:23:05,400 --> 00:23:07,660
I'll take care of you
till the day you die.

310
00:23:10,900 --> 00:23:12,030
My leg

311
00:23:12,530 --> 00:23:13,510
cannot be cured.

312
00:23:14,980 --> 00:23:15,980
One day,

313
00:23:16,770 --> 00:23:18,500
you will have to act on your own.

314
00:23:18,960 --> 00:23:20,220
I won't be by your side.

315
00:23:20,640 --> 00:23:22,440
No one will be watching over you.

316
00:23:23,240 --> 00:23:24,610
I can just quit my job.

317
00:23:24,750 --> 00:23:25,810
You are so capable.

318
00:23:27,070 --> 00:23:28,470
It'd be a pity if you quit.

319
00:23:29,080 --> 00:23:30,880
What's the use of being capable?

320
00:23:31,110 --> 00:23:32,570
I made you end up like this.

321
00:23:34,790 --> 00:23:36,140
Actually, it's not too late

322
00:23:36,140 --> 00:23:37,480
for you to understand all this now.

323
00:23:37,480 --> 00:23:38,780
You still have a long way to go.

324
00:23:38,780 --> 00:23:40,580
You have to keep moving forward.

325
00:23:44,220 --> 00:23:46,750
Just tell me what you want to say.
I'll listen.

326
00:23:47,390 --> 00:23:49,410
When you encounter something
in the future,

327
00:23:49,410 --> 00:23:50,470
you must stay calm.

328
00:23:50,930 --> 00:23:52,130
Never act on impulse.

329
00:23:53,640 --> 00:23:56,570
Think about
how it will affect the people around you.

330
00:23:56,700 --> 00:23:57,350
Got it.

331
00:24:15,550 --> 00:24:16,360
I'm sorry.

332
00:24:26,030 --> 00:24:26,760
Look at this.

333
00:24:27,530 --> 00:24:28,310
Do you like it?

334
00:24:28,310 --> 00:24:29,320
No, thank you.

335
00:24:37,970 --> 00:24:39,300
Newspaper! Newspaper!

336
00:24:39,300 --> 00:24:41,680
Mysterious toxic plant spreads rapidly.

337
00:24:41,710 --> 00:24:44,710
-Many people have died of poisoning in Xucheng!
-Kid.

338
00:24:45,060 --> 00:24:46,260
I'll get a newspaper.

339
00:24:47,720 --> 00:24:49,000
Newspaper! Newspaper!

340
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:51,610
Mysterious toxic plant spreads rapidly.

341
00:24:50,250 --> 00:24:51,540
[Nanyang Daily]

342
00:24:51,720 --> 00:24:54,870
Many people have died
of poisoning in Xucheng!

343
00:24:57,910 --> 00:24:59,440
We've got business. Hurry.

344
00:25:01,050 --> 00:25:02,320
Look at this.

345
00:25:03,070 --> 00:25:04,250
Is it exactly what I thought?

346
00:25:04,250 --> 00:25:06,030
We're out of money. Why are you
buying so many newspapers?

347
00:25:06,030 --> 00:25:08,560
Didn't I pick up a bunch
of newspapers for you?

348
00:25:12,480 --> 00:25:13,750
A bizarre disease suddenly

349
00:25:13,750 --> 00:25:14,980
broke out in Xucheng.

350
00:25:15,030 --> 00:25:16,780
Resembles...

351
00:25:17,250 --> 00:25:17,860
[Resembles a dandelion]

352
00:25:20,920 --> 00:25:22,350
A large number of red rashes
appear all over the body,

353
00:25:22,180 --> 00:25:22,820
[It is highly lethal]

354
00:25:22,380 --> 00:25:23,690
accompanied by ulceration.

355
00:25:23,690 --> 00:25:24,190
[Some victims may die instantly]

356
00:25:23,850 --> 00:25:26,090
Death occurs rapidly after inhalation.

357
00:25:26,090 --> 00:25:27,110
Twilight Grass.

358
00:25:27,850 --> 00:25:29,110
It's been three years.

359
00:25:30,290 --> 00:25:31,940
We are the only two

360
00:25:32,110 --> 00:25:33,330
who survived the Panhua Reef,

361
00:25:33,330 --> 00:25:34,590
apart from those warlords.

362
00:25:34,590 --> 00:25:36,590
I've been looking up information
on the Twilight Grass all these years,

363
00:25:36,590 --> 00:25:37,750
but with no results.

364
00:25:38,440 --> 00:25:40,040
Now it has finally appeared.

365
00:25:40,530 --> 00:25:42,000
Those bastards are back.

366
00:25:45,530 --> 00:25:47,000
What are they up to?

367
00:25:49,010 --> 00:25:51,940
The Evil God case was connected
to the warlords, too.

368
00:25:52,720 --> 00:25:54,720
Maybe these two things are related.

369
00:26:03,530 --> 00:26:04,310
Forget it.

370
00:26:05,220 --> 00:26:07,140
The Archives are gone.
Why should I investigate?

371
00:26:07,140 --> 00:26:08,800
What does it have to do with me?

372
00:26:14,270 --> 00:26:16,250
The shipping in Nanyang
is very developed now.

373
00:26:16,250 --> 00:26:18,810
Thousands of people
pass through every dock every day.

374
00:26:18,810 --> 00:26:20,700
If it really is the Twilight Grass,

375
00:26:20,700 --> 00:26:21,810
those stamens,

376
00:26:22,000 --> 00:26:23,730
filaments, and seeds

377
00:26:23,770 --> 00:26:25,140
will be brought to various places.

378
00:26:25,140 --> 00:26:26,510
They are all highly toxic

379
00:26:26,510 --> 00:26:28,500
and will endanger ordinary people.

380
00:26:28,500 --> 00:26:30,680
Although we haven't been paid
for a long time,

381
00:26:30,680 --> 00:26:31,410
the Archives

382
00:26:31,420 --> 00:26:33,350
still has a duty to issue warnings.

383
00:26:33,830 --> 00:26:36,830
You don't want those people
to suffer, either, do you?

384
00:26:40,160 --> 00:26:41,890
Why don't you go and take a look?

385
00:26:45,540 --> 00:26:46,850
I'll be back quickly.

386
00:27:08,010 --> 00:27:12,080
[The Xucheng Twilight Grass Poison Case]

387
00:28:28,880 --> 00:28:29,620
Shrimpie.

388
00:28:32,830 --> 00:28:34,030
We're here. Get down.

389
00:28:37,240 --> 00:28:38,270
Wait here a minute.

390
00:28:38,270 --> 00:28:39,670
I'll go get a seat for you.

391
00:28:41,570 --> 00:28:42,670
What's going on?

392
00:28:43,030 --> 00:28:44,890
Don't worry. She's not poisoned.

393
00:28:45,460 --> 00:28:47,440
I waited for her
outside the city for three days.

394
00:28:47,440 --> 00:28:48,920
She's already been disinfected

395
00:28:48,920 --> 00:28:49,830
and bathed.

396
00:28:51,310 --> 00:28:52,790
We're both familiar with this poison.

397
00:28:52,790 --> 00:28:54,050
If she were poisoned,

398
00:28:54,160 --> 00:28:56,750
ulceration would definitely appear
within three days.

399
00:28:56,750 --> 00:28:57,410
Have a seat.

400
00:29:01,660 --> 00:29:02,860
She's Zhang Haijiao.

401
00:29:04,180 --> 00:29:05,580
Call him Uncle Shrimpie.

402
00:29:05,720 --> 00:29:06,880
Uncle Shrimpie.

403
00:29:11,460 --> 00:29:13,320
You named the younger generation

404
00:29:13,460 --> 00:29:15,010
using characters from our own generation?

405
00:29:15,010 --> 00:29:15,960
Mentor said

406
00:29:16,070 --> 00:29:18,460
that those living abroad can take "Hai"
as their generation name

407
00:29:18,460 --> 00:29:21,290
to signify their separation from home
and their wandering lives.

408
00:29:21,290 --> 00:29:22,220
Are you thirsty?

409
00:29:23,680 --> 00:29:26,540
Separation from home
and their wandering lives...

410
00:29:32,850 --> 00:29:34,220
My name is Zhang Haixia.

411
00:29:35,530 --> 00:29:37,190
"Xia," as in a wandering hero.

412
00:29:38,770 --> 00:29:40,170
His name is Zhang Hailou.

413
00:29:40,330 --> 00:29:41,390
"Lou," as in tower.

414
00:29:41,640 --> 00:29:43,640
Listening to the spring rain
through the night in a little tower.

415
00:29:43,640 --> 00:29:46,100
A wandering hero of Xianyang
for many years.

416
00:29:47,960 --> 00:29:49,290
Is that a line of poetry?

417
00:29:50,420 --> 00:29:51,700
I meant for you to fan her.

418
00:29:51,700 --> 00:29:52,160
Fine.

419
00:29:56,980 --> 00:29:58,240
To welcome Haijiao,

420
00:29:58,460 --> 00:29:59,990
we are having hotpot today.

421
00:30:06,640 --> 00:30:08,170
Thank you, Uncle Shrimpie.

422
00:30:10,370 --> 00:30:11,900
Thank you, Uncle Shrimpie.

423
00:30:32,590 --> 00:30:33,510
These three villages

424
00:30:33,510 --> 00:30:36,310
were the first places where Twilight Grass
spread simultaneously.

425
00:30:36,310 --> 00:30:37,470
In there,

426
00:30:37,290 --> 00:30:38,990
[When did they get poisoned?]
[July 2] [First Victim]

427
00:30:37,700 --> 00:30:38,840
the first victims

428
00:30:38,870 --> 00:30:40,700
all had boarded Nan'an

429
00:30:39,110 --> 00:30:42,440
[The Nan'an]

430
00:30:40,880 --> 00:30:43,540
from Xiacheng to Balai
in the first week of July.

431
00:30:48,740 --> 00:30:50,420
I've checked the news in Xiacheng—

432
00:30:50,420 --> 00:30:52,160
no one was poisoned by the Twilight Grass.

433
00:30:52,160 --> 00:30:53,040
This means

434
00:30:53,090 --> 00:30:55,800
these three people must
have been poisoned aboard the ship.

435
00:30:55,800 --> 00:30:56,650
You can take a closer look

436
00:30:56,160 --> 00:30:58,050
[Yeruicheng] [Yungangyi] [Langhuacheng]

437
00:30:56,680 --> 00:30:58,120
at the locations of these villages.

438
00:30:58,120 --> 00:30:59,670
[Balai] [Xucheng]

439
00:30:59,610 --> 00:31:01,090
They are evenly
distributed around Xucheng.

440
00:30:59,670 --> 00:31:08,540
[Yeruicheng] [Yungangyi] [Langhuacheng]

441
00:31:02,050 --> 00:31:02,740
I think someone

442
00:31:02,740 --> 00:31:04,380
deliberately found these three people

443
00:31:04,380 --> 00:31:05,780
and had them carry Twilight Grass Poison

444
00:31:05,780 --> 00:31:07,140
back to their villages at the same time,

445
00:31:07,140 --> 00:31:08,250
so that the toxic weed could spread

446
00:31:08,250 --> 00:31:09,580
as quickly as possible.

447
00:31:09,850 --> 00:31:10,780
If this incident

448
00:31:11,160 --> 00:31:13,740
was also the work of the warlord
who dug up the Twilight Grass back then,

449
00:31:13,740 --> 00:31:15,830
their people are likely on Nan'an.

450
00:31:16,920 --> 00:31:19,060
[When did they get poisoned?]
[July 2] [First Victim]

451
00:31:32,680 --> 00:31:34,880
Since all clues now point to Nan'an,

452
00:31:36,140 --> 00:31:38,470
should we get on the ship and investigate?

453
00:31:39,220 --> 00:31:40,330
When will it dock again?

454
00:31:40,330 --> 00:31:40,930
Next week.

455
00:31:45,660 --> 00:31:47,320
The Nan'an heads to Xiacheng.

456
00:31:47,660 --> 00:31:49,180
If you want to investigate,

457
00:31:49,180 --> 00:31:50,640
you have to go the whole way

458
00:31:51,110 --> 00:31:52,440
and get off at Xiacheng.

459
00:32:01,250 --> 00:32:03,030
The tickets for Nan'an
are very expensive.

460
00:32:03,030 --> 00:32:05,050
Even with a one-way steerage ticket,

461
00:32:05,050 --> 00:32:07,140
our money is only enough for one.

462
00:32:07,420 --> 00:32:08,840
And by the time you come back,

463
00:32:08,840 --> 00:32:10,100
it will be a year later,

464
00:32:10,110 --> 00:32:10,690
right?

465
00:32:10,980 --> 00:32:12,050
You don't need to worry about that.

466
00:32:12,050 --> 00:32:13,780
I've already thought about it.

467
00:32:15,400 --> 00:32:16,600
If we sell this place,

468
00:32:16,660 --> 00:32:18,680
we can buy two tickets
and go back to Xiacheng together.

469
00:32:18,680 --> 00:32:19,240
And

470
00:32:19,810 --> 00:32:21,330
we can return to Xiacheng
in the name of investigating a case.

471
00:32:21,330 --> 00:32:22,510
That way, we definitely won't
be considered deserters.

472
00:32:22,510 --> 00:32:23,730
Sell the Archives?

473
00:32:24,350 --> 00:32:25,940
How could you come up with such an idea?

474
00:32:25,940 --> 00:32:26,510
Why not?

475
00:32:26,540 --> 00:32:27,980
Why don't you just sell me instead?

476
00:32:27,980 --> 00:32:30,840
Hey, this place has
been abandoned for three years.

477
00:32:30,880 --> 00:32:32,530
They are just worldly possessions.

478
00:32:32,530 --> 00:32:35,130
We have to think
about the living first, right?

479
00:32:39,110 --> 00:32:39,850
You go back.

480
00:32:42,030 --> 00:32:44,890
Go back and check
why our salaries haven't arrived.

481
00:32:45,160 --> 00:32:47,160
And visit Mentor while you're at it.

482
00:32:54,840 --> 00:32:56,700
If the Southern Archives is gone,

483
00:32:59,770 --> 00:33:00,830
don't come back.

484
00:33:06,210 --> 00:33:07,270
Send me a telegram,

485
00:33:08,510 --> 00:33:09,640
and we'll part ways.

486
00:33:09,980 --> 00:33:10,910
Absolutely not.

487
00:33:11,510 --> 00:33:13,170
We agreed to go back together.

488
00:33:13,510 --> 00:33:15,840
It would be so awkward
if I went back alone.

489
00:33:16,550 --> 00:33:18,480
And the money belongs to both of us.

490
00:33:18,530 --> 00:33:19,460
You have a share.

491
00:33:25,500 --> 00:33:26,630
I've made up my mind.

492
00:33:26,930 --> 00:33:27,990
I'm not going back.

493
00:33:29,570 --> 00:33:30,570
You go back for me.

494
00:33:31,460 --> 00:33:34,060
There's no need
to waste your life here with me.

495
00:33:37,380 --> 00:33:38,070
Forget it.

496
00:33:39,530 --> 00:33:42,130
I'll investigate
those three villages first.

497
00:33:43,530 --> 00:33:44,660
Maybe you're right.

498
00:33:46,590 --> 00:33:49,320
This way, neither of us
has to go back to Xiacheng.

499
00:33:50,460 --> 00:33:51,190
That's good.

500
00:34:08,050 --> 00:34:08,610
Hailou,

501
00:34:09,130 --> 00:34:10,790
you still have a long way to go.

502
00:34:11,020 --> 00:34:12,820
You have to keep moving forward.

503
00:34:14,260 --> 00:34:16,719
When we get back
to Xiacheng and find Mentor,

504
00:34:16,750 --> 00:34:18,949
I'm sure she'll be able to cure your leg.

505
00:34:43,780 --> 00:34:45,580
You've already switched sides?

506
00:34:46,510 --> 00:34:48,770
Have you forgotten who brought you back?

507
00:34:49,380 --> 00:34:50,510
Uncle Shrimpie said

508
00:34:50,630 --> 00:34:52,760
you really want to go back to Xiacheng.

509
00:34:53,010 --> 00:34:55,860
It's not easy to have something
you want to do in mind.

510
00:34:55,860 --> 00:34:57,190
He envies you very much.

511
00:34:57,260 --> 00:34:58,790
So you want to drive me away?

512
00:34:59,030 --> 00:34:59,880
Didn't you say

513
00:35:00,380 --> 00:35:01,460
you brought me back

514
00:35:01,500 --> 00:35:03,900
just to serve Uncle Shrimpie
like my own father?

515
00:35:03,900 --> 00:35:05,430
I will take good care of him.

516
00:35:05,730 --> 00:35:07,990
You can leave without worrying about us.

517
00:35:08,610 --> 00:35:10,870
Did Shrimpie Zhang teach you to say that?

518
00:35:13,800 --> 00:35:15,440
This is also my own idea.

519
00:35:16,300 --> 00:35:19,070
In the future, Uncle Shrimpie
and I will depend on each other.

520
00:35:19,070 --> 00:35:20,650
We will work hard on our business.

521
00:35:20,650 --> 00:35:22,110
When we save enough money,

522
00:35:22,300 --> 00:35:24,360
we will come to Xiacheng
to reunite with you.

523
00:35:24,360 --> 00:35:26,090
You can leave without worrying about us.

524
00:35:26,090 --> 00:35:27,490
We won't die without you.

525
00:35:36,260 --> 00:35:38,460
Zhang Haixia, what's the point of this?

526
00:35:42,530 --> 00:35:43,500
You're not dead.

527
00:35:47,440 --> 00:35:48,450
You were expelled from the Archives,

528
00:35:48,450 --> 00:35:50,850
and you still have the nerve
to show up here?

529
00:35:51,130 --> 00:35:52,230
Do I have to send you to prison,

530
00:35:52,230 --> 00:35:53,630
or will you go on your own?

531
00:35:55,690 --> 00:35:56,690
Don't act rashly.

532
00:35:58,460 --> 00:35:59,860
Call him Mr. Zhang Ruipu.

533
00:36:00,360 --> 00:36:01,760
According to seniority,

534
00:36:01,860 --> 00:36:03,390
he is even Mentor's senior.

535
00:36:14,380 --> 00:36:17,040
I heard you're looking
into the Twilight Grass.

536
00:36:17,820 --> 00:36:19,550
So I came specifically to help.

537
00:36:23,670 --> 00:36:24,600
Long time no see.

538
00:36:41,670 --> 00:36:43,330
A master from the common folk?

539
00:36:44,860 --> 00:36:46,660
Turns out you're actually poor.

540
00:36:46,960 --> 00:36:49,290
Mr. Zhang, beat us
or kill us as you please.

541
00:36:49,530 --> 00:36:50,690
Why mock us?

542
00:36:51,190 --> 00:36:53,010
I just think your spirit is commendable.

543
00:36:53,010 --> 00:36:55,470
So poor, yet you
still work for the Archives.

544
00:36:57,570 --> 00:36:58,360
Actually, the first time

545
00:36:58,360 --> 00:37:00,420
you appeared under that saline lake,

546
00:37:00,960 --> 00:37:02,760
I had already known who you were.

547
00:37:03,170 --> 00:37:05,230
But I felt that with your qualities,

548
00:37:05,860 --> 00:37:07,480
you'd never catch me.

549
00:37:07,730 --> 00:37:09,190
So I didn't eliminate you,

550
00:37:09,500 --> 00:37:10,840
lest the Southern Archives

551
00:37:10,840 --> 00:37:12,300
send some reliable people

552
00:37:13,260 --> 00:37:15,060
and leave me no peace in Xucheng.

553
00:37:16,190 --> 00:37:17,000
As a result,

554
00:37:17,500 --> 00:37:19,030
living up to expectations,

555
00:37:19,050 --> 00:37:20,780
you were even more incompetent

556
00:37:21,300 --> 00:37:22,710
than I expected.

557
00:37:24,340 --> 00:37:27,050
Actually, last time, we were
investigating the Evil God Case.

558
00:37:27,050 --> 00:37:28,710
Tricking you was just a bonus.

559
00:37:29,600 --> 00:37:30,300
By the way,

560
00:37:30,670 --> 00:37:31,980
how much do you know

561
00:37:31,980 --> 00:37:34,180
about this Twilight Grass Poison case?

562
00:37:44,650 --> 00:37:46,130
Don't waste my time.

563
00:37:46,260 --> 00:37:47,070
Zhang Hailou.

564
00:37:48,050 --> 00:37:50,360
Twilight Grass hasn't appeared
for hundreds of years.

565
00:37:50,360 --> 00:37:52,490
This time, it suddenly
broke out in Xucheng,

566
00:37:52,490 --> 00:37:55,020
yet you came back alive
from a heap of corpses.

567
00:37:55,230 --> 00:37:56,190
As far as I know,

568
00:37:56,260 --> 00:37:58,230
only those who have been
exposed to Twilight Grass

569
00:37:58,230 --> 00:38:01,110
can develop
an alkaloid barrier in their bodies.

570
00:38:01,550 --> 00:38:03,110
How were you exposed to it?

571
00:38:14,900 --> 00:38:17,760
Your brother-in-arms
was crippled because of you.

572
00:38:18,570 --> 00:38:20,630
You've taken care of him until now...

573
00:38:22,210 --> 00:38:23,710
Are you a bit tired of it?

574
00:38:25,840 --> 00:38:27,170
If there's an accident,

575
00:38:28,210 --> 00:38:29,130
for example,

576
00:38:30,440 --> 00:38:31,780
I help you kill him,

577
00:38:39,820 --> 00:38:42,050
would your life be a bit easier?

578
00:38:55,170 --> 00:38:56,440
Since you were from the Archives,

579
00:38:56,440 --> 00:38:58,170
you should know the rules of it.

580
00:39:00,510 --> 00:39:03,040
The Southern Archives' rule
has always been:

581
00:39:03,050 --> 00:39:04,180
what must not be said

582
00:39:04,690 --> 00:39:07,620
will not be said,
even if one's closest kin dies right

583
00:39:08,780 --> 00:39:09,840
before their eyes.

584
00:39:10,360 --> 00:39:12,220
How can you threaten me with this?

585
00:39:13,150 --> 00:39:13,980
You keep him.

586
00:39:15,150 --> 00:39:15,880
I'm leaving.

587
00:39:43,050 --> 00:39:43,880
Zhang Ruipu!

588
00:40:19,170 --> 00:40:20,480
How touching.

589
00:40:21,830 --> 00:40:22,710
I'm envious.

590
00:40:25,340 --> 00:40:27,020
Then I suppose it's time
to start extracting answers.

591
00:40:27,020 --> 00:40:28,210
Answer me,

592
00:40:29,130 --> 00:40:30,790
or I start snapping his spine,

593
00:40:30,790 --> 00:40:32,550
vertebrae by vertebrae.

594
00:40:33,010 --> 00:40:34,740
For every minute you hesitate,

595
00:40:35,710 --> 00:40:37,070
I'll crush another one.

596
00:40:38,510 --> 00:40:40,300
Right now, his arms still have feeling.

597
00:40:40,300 --> 00:40:41,750
In seven minutes,

598
00:40:42,920 --> 00:40:44,390
other than his head...

599
00:40:44,940 --> 00:40:45,690
No,

600
00:40:45,820 --> 00:40:47,690
he'll only be able to move his head.
